Welcome to PyCon India 2020, the premier Python conference in India, organized by the community, for the community.

The conference will be kicking off on October 2nd, 12:00 IST (UTC+5:30) with the opening address. Join us for the event on Hopin using this [link](https://www.notion.so/pyconindia/%7B%7Bextra.redeem_link%7D%7D). You can find the updated schedule on the Hopin event page at all times. Don't forget to join our communication platform Zulip with the link [here](https://pyconindia.zulipchat.com/join/aff6nsbcmffvg5uwa3q7pqyf/) to connect and network with other conference attendees and speakers. Get the ice broken by saying hi! in the **#2020/attendees** Zulip ****stream. If you are attending for the first time, do check out the **#2020/beginners** Zulip stream.

The conference will be having 6 keynotes, 36 talks, 7 workshops, diversity sessions, Birds of a Feather, lightning talks, .extend() track, Dev Sprints, and much more. You can read more about the conference in the PyCon India Program Guide at <PPG LINK>. You can also find your conference badge on the [virtual badges](https://in.pycon.org/badges/) app, which you can edit as per your liking and show it off to your friends.

Reach out to our Help Desk on [Zulip](https://pyconindia.zulipchat.com/join/ykzqdmjnllr5xcxbroz2tmhb/) or PyCon India Helpdesk on Hopin Expo area if you have any questions or want to know more about the conference. Please make sure you follow the conference [Code of Conduct](https://in.pycon.org/2020/coc/) to make the conference a great experience for everyone.

Looking forward to meeting you at the conference.

Regards,PyCon India Team
